  "prompt": "What is the limit to follow in Instagram?",
  "response": "Instagram has several limits in place to ensure fair usage and prevent spam. Here are some key limits to be aware of:\n\n1. **Daily Follow Limit**: Instagram typically allows users to follow up to 200 new accounts per day. Exceeding this limit may result in a temporary block on your account.\n\n2. **Total Accounts Followed**: There's also a limit on the total number of accounts you can follow. Generally, this limit is around 7,500 accounts. However, Instagram may adjust this based on your account's activity and history.\n\n3. **Unfollow Limit**: Similar to the follow limit, there's also a daily unfollow limit, typically set around 200 actions per day.\n\n4. **Action Blocks**: If Instagram detects suspicious activity, such as rapidly following and unfollowing accounts, it may impose temporary action blocks, which prevent you from performing certain actions for a period of time.\n\nThese limits can vary and are subject to change, so it's a good idea to keep an eye on Instagram's official guidelines and any updates they might provide.",
